snippet.textDisplay:
I think I have my fair share of defending people so story time, I guess.
One of my friends was made fun of by basically everyone except our little friend group.
A couple kids including, and I am really ashamed of it, my brother made a habit of this, though.
They were mocking her, bringing up past actions which I don't see why they would think is something to be ashamed of... you all probably can imagine what middle schoolers think would be a good way to bring down others.
Since I get pissed as FUCK when I witness someone being treated badly, I could barely hold in my anger.
The problem is, I am also incredibly quiet and people know me as the quiet goodie two shoes and doing something as big as making a scene in public would not only ruin my reputation, I myself would regret it as I tend to overthink a lot.
One day, though, I just couldn't hold in the pure AGRESSION I felt towards these ASSHOLES.
I didn't go as far as hurting them, I yelled at them at the top of my lungs, "I swear to god, if you ever DARE to say ONE more word to ANYONE in this school with the intention of hurting them, mark my FUCKING words, I will make sure you regret it." To be fair, they were all way taller and stronger than I am and could easily defend themselves if I were to attack them, I was not afraid to do so but at a moment of my social justice warrior instincts taking over, I do not care about anything but defending others.
As I expected, I got mocking but less daring responses from all of them, as well as the entire class going quiet with a side of shocked faces.
After seeing those faces, I did regret it but not all the way.
They stopped a tiny bit and believe me, I tried my famn best to contain my anger, more than ever after that and since my parents found out, they were not happy.
They did not like the idea of me standing up to someone for some reason. They gave me a 3 hour lecture on how I should "mind my business" which still gets on my nerves.
